Welbeck beat Kasper Schmeichel with a powerful header from Neal Maupay’s cross with eight minutes remaining. Dan Burn came close to snatching a winner but his towering header was cleared off the line by Youri Tielemans, before Schmeichel made a stunning save to deny Leandro Trossard.   EPL: Arsenal draws Burnley     EPL: Liverpool beat Crystal Palace 3-1     VIDEO: Sale of Super Eagles jersey, insignia in Garoua…   Patson Daka had earlier fired Leicester in front 30 seconds into the second half after goalkeeper Robert Sanchez had parried Harvey Barnes’ shot into his path. The draw keeps Brighton in ninth place, four points clear of Leicester in 10th.